{"name": "mpbn", "metadata": {"name": "mpbn", "version": "3.8", "classifiers": ["Intended Audience :: Science/Research", "Topic :: Scientific/Engineering", "Topic :: Scientific/Engineering :: Artificial Intelligence", "Topic :: Scientific/Engineering :: Bio-Informatics"], "home_page": "https://github.com/bnediction/mpbn", "license": "CeCILL", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["boolean.py", "clingo", "colomoto-jupyter", "numpy", "pyeda", "scipy", "tqdm"], "summary": "Simple implementation of Most Permissive Boolean networks", "upload_time": 1724852777}, "documentation": ["\nThe `mpbn` Python module offers a simple implementation of reachability and attractor analysis (minimal trap spaces) in *Most Permissive Boolean Networks* ([doi:10.1038/s41467-020-18112-5](https://doi.org/10.1038/s41467-020-18112-5)). The `mpbn` Python module also offers a *Most Permissive* simulator, which provides trajectory sampling and computes attractor propensities (see paper [Variable-Depth Simulation of Most Permissive Boolean Networks](https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-3-031-15034-0_7) for more details).\n\nIt is built on the `minibn` module from [colomoto-jupyter](https://github.com/colomoto/colomoto-jupyter) which allows importation of Boolean networks in many formats. See http://colomoto.org/notebook.\n\n## Installation\n\n### CoLoMoTo Notebook environment\n\n`mpbn` is distributed in the [CoLoMoTo docker](http://colomoto.org/notebook).\n\n### Using pip\n\n```\npip install mpbn\n```\n\n### Using conda\n```\nconda install -c colomoto -c potassco mpbn\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n### Command line\n\n- Enumeration of fixed points and attractors:\n```\nmpbn -h\n```\n\n- Simulation:\n```\nmpbn-sim -h\n```\n\n### Python interface\n\nDocumentation is available at https://mpbn.readthedocs.io.\n\nExample notebooks:\n* https://nbviewer.org/github/bnediction/mpbn/tree/master/examples/\n* http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3719097\n\nFor the simulation:\n* https://nbviewer.org/github/bnediction/mpbn/blob/master/examples/Simulation.ipynb\n\n\n[1]: https://arxiv.org/abs/1808.10240\n"], "modules": [{"name": "mpbn.cli.sim", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "mpbn.cli.sim.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "mpbn.cli", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "mpbn.cli.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "mpbn.cli.ArgumentParser", "xref": {"fqname": "argparse.ArgumentParser", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "tests.test_input", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "tests.test_input.InputTest", "bases": ["unittest.TestCase"], "methods": [{"name": "tests.test_input.InputTest.test_nonmonotonic", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "mpbn.converters", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "mpbn.converters.expr2str", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "ex", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["converts a pyeda Boolean expression to string representation"]}, {"name": "mpbn.converters.bn_of_asynchronous_transition_graph", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "adyn", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "names", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "parse_node", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "bn_class", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "simplify", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Convert the transition graph of a (fully) asynchronous Boolean network to\na propositional logic representation.\n\nThe object `adyn` must be an instance of `networkx.DiGraph`.\nThe `parse_node` function must return a tuple of 0 and 1 from an `adyn`\nnode. By default, it is assumed that nodes are strings of binary values.\nReturned object will be of `bn_class`, instantiated with a dictionnary\nmapping component names to a string representation of their Boolean expression."]}], "variables": [{"name": "mpbn.converters.f", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mpbn.converters.g", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "tests.test_reachability", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "tests.test_reachability.RechabilityTest_Automata18", "bases": ["unittest.TestCase"], "methods": [{"name": "tests.test_reachability.RechabilityTest_Automata18.setUp", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_reachability.RechabilityTest_Automata18.test_c0c1", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_reachability.RechabilityTest_Automata18.test_c0ci", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_reachability.RechabilityTest_Automata18.test_cicd", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "tests", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "tests.test_attractors", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "tests.test_attractors.AttractorsTest", "bases": ["unittest.TestCase"], "methods": [{"name": "tests.test_attractors.AttractorsTest.test_automata18", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": nul