at least one configuration\nmatching with `x`\n\n```\nparam dict[str,int] x\n\ninitial configuration\n\nparam dict[str,int] y\n\ntarget configuration\n```\n"]}, {"name": "mpbn.MPBooleanNetwork._ground_rules", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "ctl", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "rules", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mpbn.MPBooleanNetwork._fixedpoints", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "reachable_from", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "constraints", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "limit", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mpbn.MPBooleanNetwork.fixedpoints", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "reachable_from", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "constraints", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "limit", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Iterator over fixed points of the MPBN (i.e., of f)\n\n```\nparam dict[str,int] reachable_from\n\nrestrict to the attractors\nreachable from the given configuration. Whenever partial, restrict\nattractors to the one reachable by at least one matching\nconfiguration.\n\nparam dict[str,int] constraints\n\nconsider only attractors matching with\nthe given constraints.\n\nparam int limit\n\nmaximum number of solutions, 0 for unlimited.\n```\n"]}, {"name": "mpbn.MPBooleanNetwork.count_fixedpoints", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "reachable_from", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "constraints", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "limit", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns number of fixed points\n\n```\nparam dict[str,int] reachable_from\n\nrestrict to the attractors\nreachable from the given configuration. Whenever partial, restrict\nattractors to the one reachable by at least one matching\nconfiguration.\n\nparam dict[str,int] constraints\n\nconsider only attractors matching with\nthe given constraints.\n\nparam int limit\n\nmaximum number of solutions, 0 for unlimited.\n```\n"]}, {"name": "mpbn.MPBooleanNetwork._trapspaces", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "reachable_from", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "subcube", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "limit", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "mode", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "exclude_full", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mpbn.MPBooleanNetwork._yield_trapspaces", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "star", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mpbn.MPBooleanNetwork._count_trapspaces", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mpbn.MPBooleanNetwork.attractors", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "reachable_from", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "constraints", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "limit", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "star", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Iterator over attractors of the MPBN (minimal trap spaces of the BN).\nAn attractor is an hypercube, represented by a dictionnary mapping every\ncomponent of the network to either `0`, `1`, or `star`.\n\n```\nparam dict[str,int] reachable_from\n\nrestrict to the attractors\nreachable from the given configuration. Whenever partial, restrict\nattractors to the one reachable by at least one matching\nconfiguration.\n\nparam dict[str,int] constraints\n\nconsider only attractors matching with\nthe given constraints.\n\nparam int limit\n\nmaximum number of solutions, 0 for unlimited.\n\nparam str star\n\nvalue to use for components which are free in the\nattractor\n```\n"]}, {"name": "mpbn.MPBooleanNetwork.maximal_trapspaces", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "limit", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "subcube", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "star", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "exclude_full", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mpbn.MPBooleanNetwork.count_attractors", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "reachable_from", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "constraints", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "limit", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns number of attractors of the MPBN (minimal trap spaces of the BN).\n\n```\nparam dict[str,int] reachable_from\n\nrestrict to the attractors\nreachable from the given configuration. Whenever partial, restrict\nattractors to the one reachable by at least one matching\nconfiguration.\n\nparam dict[str,int] constraints\n\nconsider only attractors matching with\nthe given constraints.\n\nparam int limit\n\nmaximum number of solutions, 0 for unlimited.\n```\n"]}, {"name": "mpbn.MPBooleanNetwork.count_maximal_trapspaces", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "reachable_from", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "constraints", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "limit", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns number of attractors of the MPBN (minimal trap spaces of the BN).\n\n```\nparam dict[str,int] reachable_from\n\nrestrict to the attractors\nreachable from the given configuration. Whenever partial, restrict\nattractors to the one reachable by at least one matching\nconfiguration.\n\nparam dict[str,int] constraints\n\nconsider only attractors matching with\nthe given constraints.\n\nparam int limit\n\nmaximum number of solutions, 0 for unlimited.\n```\n"]}, {"name": "mpbn.MPBooleanNetwork.has_cyclic_attractor", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mpbn.MPBooleanNetwork.reachable_from", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "x", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "reversed", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns an iterator over the configurations reachable from `x` with the\nMost Permissive update mode.\nConfiguration `x` can be partially defined: in that case a configuration\nis yielded whnever it is reachable from at least one configuration\nmatching with `x`.\n\nWhenever `reversed` is `True`, yields over the configurations that can\nreach `x` instead.\n"]}, {"name": "mpbn.MPBooleanNetwork.dynamics", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "update_mode", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns a {py:class}`networkx.DiGraph` object representing the transitions between\nthe configurations using the Most Permissive update mode by default.\nSee {py:meth}`colomoto.minibn.BooleanNetwork.dynamics`.\n"]}], "class_variables": [{"name": "mpbn.MPBooleanNetwork.supported_encodings", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mpbn.MPBooleanNetwork.dnf_encodings", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mpbn.MPBooleanNetwork.nonpc_encodings", "type": null, "docum